{"parentUuid":"0f38c8b1-cdc3-46da-b3a5-a8770e383f01","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/zhouboli/Documents/maimai-assistant","sessionId":"5a067a20-907b-43aa-8187-b6dc61bdfe4f","version":"2.1.29","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a90fa85","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014VjYf7zB8zwW3aUzTofA74","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Claude Code subagent setup configuration 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Create custom subagents - Claude Code Docs\",\"url\":\"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sub-agents\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - VoltAgent/awesome-claude-code-subagents: A collection of 100+ specialized Claude Code subagents covering a wide range of development use cases\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-claude-code-subagents\"},{\"title\":\"Best practices for Claude Code subagents\",\"url\":\"https://www.pubnub.com/blog/best-practices-for-claude-code-sub-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use Claude Code Subagents to Parallelize Development | zach wills\",\"url\":\"https://zachwills.net/how-to-use-claude-code-subagents-to-parallelize-development/\"},{\"title\":\"Practical guide to mastering Claude Code’s main agent and Sub‑agents | by md mazaharul huq | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://jewelhuq.medium.com/practical-guide-to-mastering-claude-codes-main-agent-and-sub-agents-fd52952dcf00\"},{\"title\":\"Shipyard | Claude Code Subagents Quickstart: what they are + how to use them\",\"url\":\"https://shipyard.build/blog/claude-code-subagents-guide/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - wshobson/agents: Intelligent automation and multi-agent orchestration for Claude Code\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/wshobson/agents\"},{\"title\":\"Create custom Agentic Workflows with Claude Code | by Cobus Greyling | Jan, 2026 | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://cobusgreyling.medium.com/create-custom-agentic-workflows-with-claude-code-ee49805bb28b\"},{\"title\":\"Sub-Agents Guide — claude v0.5.3\",\"url\":\"https://hexdocs.pm/claude/guide-subagents.html\"},{\"title\":\"Building with Claude Code Subagents (My Beloved Minions) | by Yee Fei | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@ooi_yee_fei/building-with-claude-code-subagents-my-beloved-minions-b5a9a4318ba5\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Claude Code subagent setup and configuration in 2026:\n\n## Getting Started with Subagents\n\nThe `/agents` command provides an interactive interface for managing subagents, allowing you to view all available subagents, create new ones with guided setup or Claude generation, and edit existing subagent configuration and tool access.\n\n## Configuration Methods\n\nYou can create subagents manually as Markdown files, define them via CLI flags, or distribute them through plugins. Subagent files use YAML frontmatter for configuration, followed by the system prompt in Markdown.\n\n## Key Setup Steps\n\nTo set up, start a Claude Code session and run the `/agents` slash command, where you'll be able to define a subagent at the project or user level. Only name and description are required in the configuration.\n\n## Configuration Options\n\nYou can configure each subagent with specific tool access rights, enabling fine-grained control over which capabilities are available for different task types. You can enforce constraints by limiting which tools a subagent can use, reuse configurations across projects with user-level subagents, specialize behavior with focused system prompts for specific domains, and control costs by routing tasks to faster, cheaper models like Haiku.\n\n## Best Practices\n\nIt's recommended to define and deploy subagents one at a time, get used to how they work, and typically max out at about 3 or 4 subagents total.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ad997bd4-1c53-4d48-b9c7-10164dc7e8ba","timestamp":"2026-02-01T04:22:58.793Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0f38c8b1-cdc3-46da-b3a5-a8770e